div.p: Proportion: An equation stating that two ratios or rates are equal.
Cross Products: For a proportion a/b = c/d, a × d = b × c.

ul.li:
Check if 3/4 = 9/12 is a proportion:
Cross products: 3 × 12 = 36 and 4 × 9 = 36.
Equal, so it is a proportion.

Scaling a recipe: 2 cups flour / 1 cup sugar = x cups flour / 2 cups sugar.
Cross products: 2 × 2 = 1 × x → x = 4.
Proportions equate two ratios or rates.
Cross products are equal in proportions.
Useful for scaling and solving unknown values.
